@andromda.service.security.permitAll (Back to Tagged Values)
Applied on: Service and service operation
Specifies whether to permit all roles to execute the opertions in the bean. This can be set on the session bean or on individual operations. If set on the session bean, all operations will inherit this behaviour. The permit all tagged value will override the roles allowed. If both are set, only the permit all tagged value is rendered.
Allowed values for this element:
true
false
@andromda.service.security.denyAll (Back to Tagged Values)
